        "release_notes": {
            "en-US": "Updated the URL for accessing CIX Forums.\nSign up for a free CIX account at <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/1b029ea73c0298821edcc8bd372d1e391de4a3daee15cee7c5cf930beb6f09f0/http%3A//forums.cix.co.uk/signUp.aspx%3Fp=cixbasic\">http://forums.cix.co.uk/signUp.aspx?p=cixbasic</a>. This takes seconds and only asks for your email address, to choose a nickname and a password. There is a activation email so the email address needs to be real."
        },
        "reviewed": null,
        "url": "https://addons.thunderbird.net/en-US/thunderbird/addon/cix-forums/versions/1.2",
        "version": "1.2"
    },
    "default_locale": "en-US",
    "description": {
        "en-US": "CIX is the original social network. Started in 1987 CIX has an active membership and over 30 years of searchable archives. Free CIX accounts are now available from <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/35db79cb1f6b290dfe28fee420d75c7a5f23a61333954e1203d0f7864b6f65f0/https%3A//forums.cix.co.uk/signUp.aspx%3F=cixbasic\">https://forums.cix.co.uk/signUp.aspx?=cixbasic</a>.\n\nThe great things about CIX are the <strong>friendly members</strong>, the fully <strong>threaded</strong> conversations, the <strong>read flags</strong> so you don't waste time reading messages you have already read.\n\nThis add-on allows you to easily access CIX Forums from Thunderbird, integrating CIX Forums with your Email client.\n\n<ul><li>Complete installation this addon and restart Thunderbird.</li><li>Right mouse click on the Help pull down menu and select Customise.</li><li>Probably at the bottom of the icons find the CIX logo.</li><li>Drag this into your toolbar, just to the right of the Help pull down is good.</li><li>Click Done.</li></ul>\nNow when you click on the CIX icon on your toolbar, CIX Forums will be launched in a new tab.\n\nWe find that once launched the font is too large. To fix this, once you have launched CIX Forums when you are looking at the Log in page, hold the CTRL key down and press the - key twice. This seems to bring clarity to the display.\n\nFor more information and free accounts, see <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://outgoing.prod.mozaws.net/v1/35db79cb1f6b290dfe28fee420d75c7a5f23a61333954e1203d0f7864b6f65f0/https%3A//forums.cix.co.uk/signUp.aspx%3F=cixbasic\">https://forums.cix.co.uk/signUp.aspx?=cixbasic</a>"
    },
